SIMPLE: subsistence
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subsistence
<hw>Sub*sist"ence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>subsistance</ets>, L. <ets>subsistentia</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Real being; existence.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Not only the things had <qex>subsistence</qex>, but the very
images were of some creatures existing.</q>
<rj><qau>Stillingfleet.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Inherency; <as>as, the <ex>subsistence</ex> of
qualities in bodies</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>That which furnishes support to animal life; means
of support; provisions, or that which produces provisions; livelihood;
<as>as, a meager <ex>subsistence</ex></as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>His viceroy could only propose to himself a comfortable
<qex>subsistence</qex> out of the plunder of his province.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>4.</sn> <fld>(Theol.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Hypostasis</er>,
2.</def> <rj><au>Hooker.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subsistence Department</ent>⟦br⟧
